annotationA: Serine--pyruvate aminotransferase; Pyridoxal phosphate binding; alanine-glyoxylate transaminase activity; serine-pyruvate transaminase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: glyoxylate catabolic process
annotationB: Putative hydroxypyruvate isomerase; Catalyzes the reversible isomerization between hydroxypyruvate and 2-hydroxy-3-oxopropanoate (also termed tartronate semialdehyde)
